<TITLE> Home ministry, REHAB to set up joint cell to curb extortion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka,May, 26 (bdnews 24.com)The home ministry and the REHAB will form a joint cell to curb extortion in the housing industry, the home minister said. "It was a courtesy meeting. But we discussed with them different issues including extortion in the housing industry," Sahara Khatun told reporters after a meeting with the executive committee members of the Real Estate and Housing Association of Bangladesh at the secretariat on Tuesday. "We have decided to set up a cell to save them from such terrorism to take immediate steps." As in the past, extortion in the housing industry and threats over mobile phones have started. In some cases, gunshots were fired, Khatun said. About the joint cell, Rehab president Tanvirul Huq Prabal said, "For some days Rehab members are being threatened for money. "Other terrorist activities are also happening to the industry. We have decided to set up a joint cell to stop these activities. The cell will consist of ten membersfive from the home ministry and five from Rehab." b
